
'''Odamea Afahyɛ''' yɛ afehyia [[afahyɛ]] a ahenfo ne wɔn manfoɔ a wɔn wɔ Nkusukum mpotam wɔ Saltpond a ɛwɔ Nfinfin Manatam wɔ Ghana no di<ref>http://www.ghanatours.net/ghana-regions/central-region/</ref><ref>https://ghana.travel/events-festivals/festivals/</ref>. Wodi saa aahye yi bosome a ɛtɔ so nwɔtwe no mu<ref>https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Nkusukum-Traditional-Council-launches-2012-Odambea-Festival-243808</ref><ref>https://tourghana.com/ghana-festivals/</ref>. Anomabo manfo nso yɛ nea wodi saa afahyɛ yi bi<ref>https://www.ghanabusinessnews.com/2016/07/17/2016-odambea-festival-launched/</ref>. ‘Odambea’’ kyerɛ ahobammɔ wɔ wɔn kasa mu

== Afa hyɛ ==
Wɔde nnuane ne nsa gye ahohoɔ wɔ afahyɛ no ase. Amanfoɔ no hyɛ wɔn amammerɛ ntadeɛ ahorɔw de kɔ dwa dataa a ahenfo no abɔ no ase. Asa ne nnwomtoɔ nso kɔ so wɔ afahyɛ no ase<ref>http://www.ghanaembassyiran.com/en/page/majorfestivals</ref>.

== Mfasoɔ ==
Wodi saa afahyɛ yi de kae tu a Nkusukufo no tu firii Techiman a ɛwɔ Bono ne Ahafo Mantam baa nea wɔte sesei no<ref>https://www.graphic.com.gh/entertainment/music/stay-jay-to-perform-at-odambea-festival.html</ref>. Wɔnam afahyɛ no so san de hyɛ asetena a na wɔte mu kane no mu kena<ref>https://www.easytrackghana.com/cultural-overview-ghana-festivals.php</ref>.
